Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @Breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @Salt{¼%tsp} and @Water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and half the garlic.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

== Rice ==

Pour the @Water{300%milliliters} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and @salt{¼%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Meatballs and Peppers ==

While the rice cooks, pop the meatballs and sliced pepper onto a #large baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if needed.

Season the peppers with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake on the top shelf of your #oven{} until the meatballs are browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Creamy Tomato Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%secs}, then pour in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton} and @Water{75%milliliters} for the sauce.

Add the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Sugar{½%tsp} for the sauce, bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once the peppers and meatballs are cooked, add them to the sauce and stir to combine.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams} into the tomato sauce and bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with your meatballs in tomato sauce and drizzle over the @Pesto{32%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!